article.description: Green Bay beats UALR in Holiday Hoops opener, 66-46
article.headline: Green Bay beats UALR in Holiday Hoops opener, 66-46
article.linkText: Green Bay beats UALR in Holiday Hoops opener, 66-46
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- Jordan Fouse scored 17 points and grabbed nine rebounds, and Alfonzo McKinnie added 16 point with 10 boards to help Green Bay roll to a 66-46 victory over Arkansas-Little Rock in the opening round of the Las Vegas Holiday Hoops Classic on Sunday. Fouse was 6 of 8 from the floor and had nine rebounds. McKinnie was 7-of-9 shooting while Carrington Love chipped in 13 points and five assists, and Keifer Sykes dished out six assists and had eight rebounds for the Phoenix. Green Bay (9-2) has won four-straight and eight of its past nine games, with the defense holding opponents under 55 points in four of the games during the streak. Roger Woods scored 18 points with eight rebounds, and James Reid had 14 points and six boards to lead Arkansas-Little Rock (4-5), which shot just 18 of 52 for 34.6 percent from the floor.
